Package trespass.annotation

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Cast
    This annotation should be used when parameter types required in the signature of a method defined in a proxy interface to make it match a corresponding method declared in the target class are not accessible to the proxy interface.
    DefaultInstanceProvider
    This annotation will optionally mark the one method in an interface extending Trespasser that will be used to obtain the default instance of a target class.
    ProxyClass
    This annotation is mandatory for proxy interfaces extending Trespasser and defines the target class for the proxy interface.
    ProxyField
    Annotate methods in an interface extending Trespasser in order to give the method the semantics of a field accessor to the named field declared in the target class
